    "In low-data bioactivity prediction, active learning can remarkably outperform traditional machine learning approaches, leading to several fold improvement in hit retrieval [26].",
    "In de novo design, active learning has (to the best of our knowledge) not been extensively explored yet.",
    "Nevertheless, active learning requires both experimental and computational resources and expertise, which might increase the barriers for its adoption.",
    "Context-enriched trainingIn this minireview, we define context-enriched training as an umbrella term encompassing approaches that provide additional knowledge to the model ('context') to improve its performance on a given task.",
    "Unlike multistage learning, in context-enriched training all available information is provided to the model simultaneously."
